<p class="line-length line-length-xl">
Color palettes give you a full spectrum of colors to use in your project.
</p>

<p class="line-length line-length-xl">
A color palette defines 10 hues, each with a scale of 11 tints. Tints are assigned numbers that correlate to their lightness. While the tints have similar lightness values across palettes, each palette has unique hue shifts and chroma so you can find just the right vibe to your project.
</p>

<p class="line-length line-length-xl">
There are 9 specially crafted color palettes; 3 are free to use with an additional 6 available in Web Awesome Pro.
</p>

{% include "theming/color-palette-picker.njk" %}

<h2>Using This Palette</h2>

<div id="import-code">
  {% for palette in themer.palettes %}
    <div class="palette-instructions" data-palette="{{ palette.name | lower }}" {% if not loop.first %}hidden{% endif %}>
      <wa-tab-group data-install-tabs>
        <wa-tab panel="cdn"><wa-icon name="globe" variant="regular"></wa-icon> CDN</wa-tab>
        <wa-tab panel="npm"><wa-icon name="box-open" variant="regular"></wa-icon> npm</wa-tab>
        <wa-tab panel="self-hosted"><wa-icon name="arrow-down-to-line" variant="regular"></wa-icon> Self-Hosted</wa-tab>
        <wa-tab panel="hosted"><wa-icon name="rocket-launch" variant="regular"></wa-icon> Hosted Projects</wa-tab>

        <wa-tab-panel name="cdn">
{% if palette.isPro %}
{% markdown %}
<wa-callout variant="neutral" size="s">
  <wa-icon slot="icon" name="info-circle" variant="regular"></wa-icon>
  This palette can only be used with a Pro subscription. {% raw %}{% if session.isLoggedIn %}{% endraw %}For instructions unique to your Pro project, open a project from <a href="/workspaces">your workspace</a>.{% raw %}{% endif %}{% endraw %}
</wa-callout>
{% endmarkdown %}
{% else %}
{% set paletteCdnUrl %}{% cdnUrl 'styles/color/palettes/' %}{{ palette.filename }}{% endset %}
{% markdown %}
To use this palette, add the palette's stylesheet from the CDN:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ paletteCdnUrl }}">
```

Then, apply the following class to the `<html>` element:

```html
<html class="wa-palette-{{ palette.name | lower }}">
```
{% endmarkdown %}
{% endif %}
        </wa-tab-panel>

        <wa-tab-panel name="npm">
{% markdown %}
After installing <code>@awesome.me/webawesome</code>, import the palette's stylesheet:

```js
import '@awesome.me/webawesome/dist/styles/color/palettes/{{ palette.filename }}';
```

Then, apply the following class to the `<html>` element:

```html
<html class="wa-palette-{{ palette.name | lower }}">
```
{% endmarkdown %}
        </wa-tab-panel>

        <wa-tab-panel name="self-hosted">
{% markdown %}
If you're self-hosting Web Awesome, include the palette's stylesheet from your server:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/dist/styles/color/palettes/{{ palette.filename }}">
```

Then, apply the following class to the `<html>` element:

```html
<html class="wa-palette-{{ palette.name | lower }}">
```
{% endmarkdown %}
        </wa-tab-panel>

        <wa-tab-panel name="hosted">
{% if palette.isPro %}
{% markdown %}
**For projects in <wa-badge appearance="accent" pill class="pro">Pro</wa-badge> workspaces:**
1. Go to your project's <wa-icon name="gear" variant="regular"></wa-icon> **Settings**.
2. Press <wa-icon name="paintbrush" variant="regular"></wa-icon> **Edit Your Theme** to open the Theme Builder.
3. Open **Colors** and select **{{ palette.name | capitalize }}**.
4. Save your theme to immediately update anywhere you're using your project.
{% endmarkdown %}
{% else %}
{% markdown %}
**For projects in <wa-badge appearance="filled" variant="neutral" pill class="free">Free</wa-badge> workspaces:**
1. Go to your project's <wa-icon name="gear" variant="regular"></wa-icon> **Settings**.
2. Find **Color Palette**. Select <wa-icon name="swatchbook" variant="regular"></wa-icon> **{{ palette.name | capitalize }}**.
3. Save your theme to immediately update anywhere you're using your project.

**For projects in <wa-badge appearance="accent" pill class="pro">Pro</wa-badge> workspaces:**
1. Go to your project's <wa-icon name="gear" variant="regular"></wa-icon> **Settings**.
2. Press <wa-icon name="paintbrush" variant="regular"></wa-icon> **Edit Your Theme** to open the Theme Builder.
3. Open **Colors** and select **{{ palette.name | capitalize }}**.
4. Save your theme to immediately update anywhere you're using your project.
{% endmarkdown %}
{% endif %}
        </wa-tab-panel>
      </wa-tab-group>
    </div>
  {% endfor %}
</div>